final_output_text: To delete a folder in a Windows laptop, there are two common methods. Here's a step-by-step explanation of both methods:

**Solution 0: Right-click the folder and select delete.**

1. Locate the folder you want to delete on your Windows laptop.
2. Place your cursor on the folder until it becomes highlighted.
3. Right-click on the folder with your mouse. This will bring up a context menu.
4. From the context menu, select the "Delete" option. This will open a confirmation dialog box.
