final_output_text: To protect a garden from ice frost, we need to consider the effectiveness of each solution in retaining heat and preventing damage to the plants. 

Solution 0: Place bed sheet on soil. 
This method involves laying a bed sheet directly on the soil surface. The sheet acts as an insulator, trapping the heat from the soil and preventing it from escaping into the cold air. This can help to keep the soil warm and protect the roots of the plants from freezing temperatures. However, this method may not be as effective as other solutions, as the sheet may not provide sufficient insulation for the entire garden, and it may not be as durable as other materials.

Solution 1: Place bed sheet over garden. 
This method involves laying a bed sheet over the entire garden, covering all the plants and soil. This provides a more comprehensive layer of insulation, trapping the heat from the soil and preventing it from escaping into the cold air. The sheet also acts as a barrier, protecting the plants from wind and frost. This method is more effective than Solution 0, as it provides a more complete and durable layer of insulation.

Considering the effectiveness and durability of the two solutions, Solution 1 is the better option for protecting a garden from ice frost. 

The answer is 1.
